Czech Stocks: CEZ, New World Resources, Telefonica Shares Move

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-08-15T14:55:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/czech-stocks-new-world-resources-telefonica-shares-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s PX stock index
gained the most in more than eight months, rising 1,016.8 at its
4:28 p.m. close in Prague.  The following were among the most active equities on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  CEZ AS (CEZ)   pared an advance of as much as 3.2 percent
after the country’s biggest power producer reported a second-
quarter profit that missed analyst estimates. The stock closed
up 0.1 percent to 753 koruna.  New World Resources Plc (NWR CP), the biggest Czech coking-
coal producer, jumped 8.1 percent to 174.99 koruna, adding to a
1.9 percent gain in the previous session.  Europe ’s benchmark
coal derivatives rose for a fourth day in Amsterdam.  Telefonica Czech Republic AS (SPTT CP) fell for a third day
after the country’s largest phone operator was cut to BBB+ from
A- at  Standard & Poor’s  on Aug. 11. The stock closed 0.5 percent
down to 400 koruna.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  